9 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to require the
10 Agency of Commerce and Community Development to establish a voluntary
11 buyout program for flood-prone properties that are either ineligible for Federal
12 Emergency Management Agency buyouts or identified by municipalities for
13 flood-resilient redevelopment or floodplain restoration. This bill also proposes
14 to create a homeowner assistance program providing financial support for
15 elevating homes in flood-prone areas, relocating displaced residents to
16 permanent housing, and rebuilding homes using flood-resilient materials and
17 designs.
